# KnowledgeVault

## Document Repository Module PRD

Version: 1.0

Status: Development Ready

---

# Overview

The Document Repository Module provides centralized storage, organization, viewing, versioning, and metadata management for business documents.

This module serves as the foundation of the KnowledgeVault platform and is intentionally independent of AI, RAG, embeddings, and semantic search capabilities.

The primary objective is to establish a secure, searchable repository of documents that can later be enhanced with AI features.

---

# Goals

Provide users with the ability to:

* Upload documents
* Organize documents into collections
* Store metadata
* View documents
* Download documents
* Manage document versions
* Search documents by metadata
* Maintain audit history

---

# Out of Scope

The following are explicitly excluded:

* AI Chat
* RAG
* Embeddings
* OCR
* Semantic Search
* LLM Integration
* Vector Databases

---

# User Roles

## Administrator

Permissions:

* Create collections
* Edit collections
* Delete collections
* Upload documents
* Delete documents
* Manage metadata
* Manage versions

---

## Contributor

Permissions:

* Upload documents
* Edit metadata
* Upload new document versions
* View documents
* Download documents

---

## Viewer

Permissions:

* View documents
* Download documents
* Search documents

---

# Collections

Collections provide logical grouping of documents.

Examples:

* Service Manuals
* Engineering Documents
* Safety Procedures
* Quality Documents
* HR Policies

---

# Collection Fields

| Field        | Required |
| ------------ | -------- |
| Name         | Yes      |
| Description  | No       |
| Active Flag  | Yes      |
| Created Date | Yes      |

---

# Collection Features

Users can:

* Create collection
* Edit collection
* Archive collection
* View collection details
* View documents within collection

---

# Documents

A document represents a logical business document.

Examples:

* Hydraulic Service Manual
* Safety Policy
* Engineering Specification

---

# Document Fields

| Field           | Required |
| --------------- | -------- |
| Title           | Yes      |
| Collection      | Yes      |
| Description     | No       |
| Status          | Yes      |
| Current Version | Yes      |
| Created Date    | Yes      |

---

# Document Metadata

Each document may contain metadata.

Supported Metadata Fields:

* Product
* Revision
* Department
* Manufacturer
* Tags
* Category
* Effective Date

Metadata must be editable after upload.

---

# Document Versions

A document may contain multiple versions.

Example:

Hydraulic Manual

* Version 1
* Version 2
* Version 3

Only one version is marked as current.

Historical versions remain available.

---

# Version Fields

| Field          | Required |
| -------------- | -------- |
| Version Number | Yes      |
| File Name      | Yes      |
| Upload Date    | Yes      |
| Uploaded By    | Yes      |
| File Size      | Yes      |
| Storage Path   | Yes      |

---

# Document Upload

Supported Formats

* PDF
* DOCX
* TXT
* HTML
* CSV
* MD

Future Support

* XLSX
* PPTX

---

# Upload Workflow

1. User selects collection.

2. User selects file.

3. User enters metadata.

4. System stores original file.

5. System creates document record.

6. System creates initial version record.

7. System makes document available for viewing.

---

# File Storage

Original files must always be retained.

Files must never be modified during storage.

Files are stored outside the database.

---

# Storage Structure

documents/

├── collection-id/

│   ├── document-id/

│   │   ├── v1.pdf

│   │   ├── v2.pdf

│   │   └── v3.pdf

---

# Document Viewer

The system shall support viewing PDF documents directly within the application.

Features:

* Page Navigation
* Zoom In
* Zoom Out
* Search Within Document
* Download Original File

---

# Document Detail Screen

Displays:

Document Information

Metadata

Current Version

Version History

Upload History

Actions

* View
* Download
* Upload New Version
* Edit Metadata
* Delete

---

# Search

Search supports:

* Document Title
* Collection
* Product
* Revision
* Tags
* Department
* Manufacturer

Search is metadata-based only.

No semantic search.

---

# Dashboard

Displays:

* Total Documents
* Total Collections
* Recent Uploads
* Storage Usage

---

# Audit Logging

Record:

* Document Upload
* Document Download
* Document Delete
* Metadata Updates
* Version Upload
* Collection Changes

---

# Database Entities

collections

documents

document_versions

document_metadata

audit_log

---

# Entity Relationships

Collection

→ Many Documents

Document

→ Many Versions

Document

→ One Metadata Record

Document

→ Many Audit Records

---

# API Requirements

Collection APIs

* Create Collection
* Update Collection
* Delete Collection
* List Collections

Document APIs

* Upload Document
* Get Document
* Update Document
* Delete Document
* Download Document

Version APIs

* Upload Version
* Get Versions
* Set Current Version

Metadata APIs

* Update Metadata
* Search Metadata

---

# Non-Functional Requirements

Upload Response

< 5 seconds

Document Search

< 2 seconds

Document Viewer Load

< 3 seconds

---

# Security

Role Based Access Control

Authenticated Access Only

Audit Logging Enabled

Secure File Download

---

# Acceptance Criteria

Users can:

✓ Create collections

✓ Upload documents

✓ View documents

✓ Download documents

✓ Edit metadata

✓ Manage document versions

✓ Search by metadata

✓ View audit history

✓ Manage document repository without AI dependencies

---

# Future Integration

This module is designed to support future integration with:

* OCR Services
* Embedding Services
* Vector Databases
* Semantic Search
* AI Chat
* RAG Pipelines

No future integration requirements should impact the design of this module.
